description: Fugitive diamond merchant Mehul Choksi has been apprehended in Belgium based on an extradition request from Indian authorities concerning a significant banking fraud case. While this marks progress in bringing Choksi to justice, challenges remain as Belgian courts may consider human rights issues and prison conditions in India, potentially hindering extradition efforts.
title: Choksi held in Belgium, but return a challenge

description: Following violent clashes sparked by the new waqf law, Hriday Das fled Murshidabad with his family after losing relatives and his home. Scores of others sought refuge in neighboring Jharkhand and Malda, highlighting the widespread fear and displacement. While some families have been escorted back by police, uncertainty lingers in the affected areas.
title: Fear still stalks residents who fled Murshidabad

description: A joint operation by Gujarat ATS and the Indian Coast Guard led to the seizure of over 300kg of methamphetamine, valued at Rs 1,800 crore, from the Arabian Sea. Smugglers, attempting to deliver the drugs to Tamil Nadu from Pakistan, dumped contraband into the sea when approached by the Coast Guard.
title: Guj ATS, CG seize 300kg of meth worth 1,800cr

description: Karnataka's potential increase in caste-based reservations faces legal challenges, mirroring the fate of similar laws in other states. While the Supreme Court deemed the 50% quota cap not entirely inflexible, it primarily applies to SC/ST/OBC reservations.
title: Karnataka bid to breach 50% quota cap awaits tough judicial test

description: Violence erupted in Bengal over the new waqf law, with Bhangar witnessing intense clashes where mobs attacked police, leaving 16 officers injured. The unrest, triggered by police preventing an ISF rally, contrasted with a crackdown in Murshidabad, resulting in numerous arrests and internet suspensions.
title: Net suspension extended to parts of Malda, Birbhum; don't get provoked, says Mamata
Students, experts flag big errors in JEE Main papers

description: India's political spectrum united to honor B.R. Ambedkar on his 135th birth anniversary, solidifying his position as a universally respected figure. Leaders like PM Modi and Sonia Gandhi paid floral tributes, mirroring celebrations by Ambedkar's followers.
title: Across political divide, netas unite to salute BR Ambedkar

description: Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge has branded the BJP-RSS as "enemies" of Ambedkar, alleging they only offer lip service for political gain. Kharge claimed Ambedkar blamed V.D. Savarkar for his 1952 election defeat and urged PM Modi to read Ambedkar's letter detailing this.
title: BJP, RSS are enemies of Ambedkar: Congress chief Kharge

description: A fire erupted at Lucknow's Lokbandhu Hospital on Monday night, sparking widespread panic and the urgent evacuation of over 200 patients, including those in critical condition. The blaze, suspected to be caused by a short circuit in the women's medicine and emergency ward, rapidly filled the second floor with thick smoke.
title: Fire at government hospital, over 200 patients evacuated in Lucknow

description: Following ED clearance, bank-appointed liquidators are auctioning Mehul Choksi's properties, including gems and jewellery valued at ₹150 crore. Choksi, wanted in multiple bank fraud cases, faces intensified legal proceedings after his arrest in Belgium. The ED has attached assets worth ₹2,566 crore and is pursuing his designation as a fugitive economic offender to expedite asset recovery.
title: Liquidators move to auction assets worth Rs 150 crore
Modi meets fan who walked barefoot for 14 years to see him as PM

description: Political tensions escalate in Bengal's Murshidabad as Trinamool Congress and BJP clash over ongoing violence. TMC accuses protesters of serving BJP's agenda by disrupting life, while BJP demands President's rule, citing a breakdown of law and order. TMC alleges opposition and BSF involvement in stirring unrest, aiming to divide communities.
title: TMC, BJP trade blame over Bengal unrest over waqf law
'Babasaheb effort helped awaken Hindu society': RSS chief Mohan Bhagwat

description: The Supreme Court's recent judgment on presidential powers concerning state bills has sparked debate. The court suggested the President seek its opinion on a bill's constitutionality under Article 143, even though it's not mandated. This raises concerns about judicial overreach into the legislative process and the practicality of reviewing numerous state bills.
title: Can President be forced to seek Supreme Court opinion on a bill?

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi, addressing a gathering in Hisar on Ambedkar's birth anniversary, strongly criticized the Congress party for allegedly disrespecting Dr. B.R. Ambedkar during his lifetime and attempting to erase his legacy. Modi highlighted development initiatives under the BJP government, contrasting them with the performance of Congress-led administrations.
title: Congress humiliated, distorted vision of Ambedkar: PM Modi

description: Justice B.R. Gavai emphasized the Constitution's pivotal role in maintaining India's unity and stability over the past 75 years, despite challenges. He lauded B.R. Ambedkar's contribution to uplifting marginalized communities, citing President Droupadi Murmu and PM Narendra Modi as examples.
title: India united, strong due to statute: Justice Gavai

description: Katy Perry and Lauren Sánchez were among the six women who journeyed to the edge of space aboard Blue Origin's New Shepard rocket, marking a historic all-female spaceflight. The suborbital flight provided a brief period of weightlessness, with Jeff Bezos greeting the crew upon their return. The event drew a crowd of high-profile figures, celebrating the mission as inspirational.
title: Katy Perry kisses Earth as Blue Origin Rocket returns from Space
Maharashtra stipend for 8L Ladki beneficiaries cut

description: An Olive Ridley turtle, tagged in Odisha in 2021, has made a remarkable 3,500km journey to Maharashtra's Konkan coast. This is the first recorded instance of such a long migration for the species. The turtle laid 120 eggs, challenging previous assumptions about distinct populations on India's east and west coasts, highlighting the interconnectedness of nesting sites.
title: 'Marco Polo of turtles' swims from Odisha to Maharashtra for double nesting

description: The Madhya Pradesh High Court has ruled that concealing a criminal case during job application constitutes "moral turpitude," even if the applicant is later acquitted. This decision upheld the cancellation of a job offer to Ram Bhuvan Yadav at the Itarsi ordnance factory, who had a pending criminal case he failed to disclose.
title: Not disclosing criminal case 'moral turpitude': HC

description: The Karnataka High Court has instructed Google India and its executives to provide bank guarantees covering 50% of the penalties levied for alleged FEMA violations. These penalties, totaling Rs 5.45 crore, stem from transactions involving distributor fees to Google Ireland and equipment purchases from Google US. The Enforcement Directorate claims these transactions, lacking RBI approval, constitute unauthorized commercial loans.
title: Submit bank guarantees for 50% of Rs 5cr fine over violations: HC to Google
Woman forced to take off hijab in UP, assaulted

description: Telangana has become the first state to implement sub-categorization of Scheduled Caste reservations, classifying 59 sub-castes into three groups. This move, coinciding with Dr. Ambedkar's 135th birth anniversary, allocates 1% reservation to Group I, 9% to Group II, and 5% to Group III.
title: 1st in India: Telangana effects quota within quota for SCs

description: Bengali New Year celebrations in Chittagong were cancelled for the first time in 47 years after vandalism by unidentified individuals. The incident, which involved the destruction of banners and stages, led to protests and the suspension of scheduled programs.
title: Bengali NY cancelled at Chittagong for 1st time in 47 years over vandalism

description: Donald Trump has once again blamed Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky for the ongoing war with Russia, despite the devastating consequences of the conflict. Trump also implicated President Biden and Putin, asserting their shared responsibility for the war's outbreak and continuation.
title: Donald Trump again accuses Volodymyr Zelenskyy of starting war

description: Riding high on their Doda victory, AAP is now targeting the Kashmir Valley, declaring their intention to contest the Budgam assembly bypoll. This election was triggered by Omar Abdullah's decision to vacate the seat. While AAP J&K chief Mehraj Malik aims to win, National Conference is yet to announce their candidate, with calls for a local representative.
title: AAP eyes Kashmir debut, to contest Budgam seat vacated by CM

description: London's historic Michelin-starred Indian restaurant, Veeraswamy, faces potential closure after nearly a century. The Crown Estate, owner of the building, plans to reclaim the space to expand office reception areas, refusing to renew the restaurant's lease. Owner Ranjit Mathrani is contesting the decision in court, fearing job losses and business disruption if forced to relocate without a suitable alternative.
title: Britain's Indian restaurant Veeraswamy under threat of closure. But why?

description: Chennai Super Kings snapped their five-match losing streak with a thrilling five-wicket victory over Lucknow Super Giants, fueled by MS Dhoni and Shivam Dube's explosive partnership. Chasing 167, CSK overcame a middle-order wobble, while LSG's Rishabh Pant's half-century went in vain. Dube credited Dhoni's aggressive batting for easing the pressure during the chase.
title: MS Dhoni and Shivam Dube end CSK's five-match losing streak

description: CPM MLA M Y Tarigami criticized the BJP and central government for allegedly hindering the Omar Abdullah government's functioning and demanded the restoration of statehood to Jammu and Kashmir. He highlighted the executive orders, domicile laws, and media restrictions imposed after the abrogation of Article 370. Tarigami also condemned the Waqf (Amendment) Act, fearing increased communal polarization.
title: Respect people’s mandate, allow Omar govt to function: Tarigami to Centre

description: A magnitude 5.1 earthquake struck southern California near Julian, a town close to the US-Mexico border, originating at a depth of eight miles. The quake, followed by aftershocks, caused no immediate reports of injuries or damage. Southern California is seismically active due to its location on tectonic plate boundaries, having experienced major quakes like the 1994 Northridge event.
title: 5.1 magnitude earthquake hits San Diego
China plays rare earth card as US, India dig deep
Fire breaks out at Lucknow hospital, CM Yogi takes cognisance

description: Nvidia will manufacture advanced AI chips in America. This is a first for the tech company. Production will be at TSMC facilities in Arizona. New supercomputer plants are coming up in Texas. Foxconn and Wistron are strategic partners. Full production will ramp up in 12 to 15 months. The move aims to meet growing AI chip demand.
title: In a first, Nvidia to build AI supercomputer chips entirely in US

description: 'Instant Scholar' is a Times of India initiative to make academic research accessible to a wider audience. If you are a Ph.D. scholar and would like to publish a summary of your research in this section, please share a summary and authorisation to publish it. For submission, and any question on this initiative, write to us at instantscholar@timesgroup.com
title: Instant Scholar: Marie Curie’s Phd thesis that revolutionised radioactivity research

description: Karnataka's chief minister Siddaramaiah defended the 4% quota for Muslims in public contracts, countering PM Modi's accusations of appeasement politics. Siddaramaiah asserted the move aims to uplift economically and socially disadvantaged minorities, while Deputy CM Shivakumar emphasized providing opportunities for all sections of society.
title: K'taka CM defends quota for Muslims, PM attacks 'appeasement policy'

description: Magnus Carlsen triumphed at the Freestyle Chess Grand Slam in Paris, securing the title by defeating Hikaru Nakamura 1.5–0.5 in the final. Carlsen's dominant performance earned him the $200,000 first prize, solidifying his status in this innovative format. Fabiano Caruana claimed third place, edging out Vincent Keymer and securing a spot in the upcoming Grand Slam event in the USA.
title: Magnus Carlsen clinches Freestyle Chess Grand Slam title in Paris

description: The Vancouver Canucks, led by Elias Pettersson and Quinn Hughes, are set to face the San Jose Sharks in their second-to-last regular season game. With two games remaining, they are well-positioned to finish strong. The Canucks have a deep, well-rounded lineup, with top lines led by Jake DeBrusk, Pius Suter, and Brock Boeser. They also have depth in young centres and a strong defense
title: Pettersson set to push Vancouver Canucks to pivotal game against Sharks

description: India is actively pursuing legal actions against individuals involved in major crimes and security threats. Tahawwur Rana, a suspect in the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, is being interrogated by the NIA, while efforts are underway to extradite Mehul Choksi from Belgium in connection with the PNB fraud.
title: Top 5 news: Tahawwur's NIA grilling, Mehul Choksi’s extradition & more

description: Shaik Rasheed, at 20 years and 202 days, became CSK's youngest-ever opener, surpassing Sam Curran's record. The Andhra native debuted against LSG, scoring a quickfire 27 off 19 balls, including six boundaries. His impressive start provided a solid foundation for CSK, marking only the third instance this season where they crossed 50 in the powerplay.
title: Who is Shaik Rasheed, the youngest player to open for CSK in IPL history?

description: Pohela Boishakh, the Bengali New Year, is a vibrant festival celebrated with enthusiasm by Bengali communities worldwide. It marks new beginnings with traditional feasts, colorful attire, and cultural performances. People exchange warm wishes, reconnect with their roots, and enjoy delicacies like panta bhaat and ilish maach, seeking blessings for a brighter future.
title: Bengali New Year: 75+ Pohela Boishakh greetings, wishes & quotes

description: MS Dhoni achieved a significant milestone in IPL history, becoming the first player to record 200 dismissals. The CSK captain reached this feat during a match against LSG, stumping Ayush Badoni. Dhoni's quick reflexes and awareness behind the stumps were on full display as he continues to solidify his legacy as IPL's greatest wicketkeeper.
title: Dhoni creates history, becomes first player to achieve this big feat in IPL

description: West Bengal chief minister Mamata Banerjee addressed the ongoing violence in the state, emphasizing the right to protest while urging citizens to maintain peace and avoid taking the law into their own hands. Her statement follows clashes between Indian Secular Front supporters and police in Bhangar, resulting in injuries and the torching of police vehicles after restrictions were imposed on an anti-Waqf Act rally.
title: 'Don't play games with religion': CM Mamata on anti-Waqf protests

description: Amidst escalating violence in West Bengal following anti-Waqf law protests, BJP chief Sukanta Majumdar has appealed to Governor CV Ananda Bose for intervention. Majumdar expressed grave concerns over the situation in Murshidabad, citing displacement of families and urged for peace restoration and a judicial inquiry. Chief Minister Mamata Banerjee has called for peace and unity, emphasizing religious harmony.
title: 'Intervene & restore normalcy': Bengal BJP writes to guv amid violence

description: A heated on-field clash between Jasprit Bumrah and Karun Nair during Sunday's IPL match between Delhi Capitals and Mumbai Indians sparked debate. The incident, stemming from a collision while Nair was batting, saw a visibly upset Bumrah. However, Delhi Capitals released a video showing Bumrah and Nair embracing post-match, confirming that the tension had dissipated.
title: 'Sab theek hai': Bumrah, Karun hug it out after heated exchange. Watch

description: After Ukraine president Volodymyr Zelenskyy appealed to President Trump to visit Ukraine following a fresh Russian attack on Sumy that Russia denied, Trump repeated that he has nothing to do with the Russia-Ukraine war. "President Zelenskyy and Crooked Joe Biden did an absolutely horrible job in allowing this travesty to begin. There were so many ways of preventing it from ever starting. But that is the past," he posted on Truth Social.
title: 'Biden's war, not mine': Trump after Zelenskyy's Ukraine invite

description: The US is crafting a strategy to counter China's global influence, with India playing a central role. Treasury Secretary Scott Bessent envisions a coalition with India, Japan, Vietnam, and South Korea to isolate Beijing economically. India's openness to US trade deals and rejection of Chinese investments signal a strategic alignment, though it remains intertwined with Chinese supply chains.
title: How India could be Trump's trump card in 'encircling' China

description: Salman Khan, a Bollywood icon, has been protected by his dedicated bodyguard, Shera, for almost three decades. Their bond extends beyond professional duty, with Shera considering Khan his 'Maalik' and vowing to protect him at all costs. Shera's loyalty is unwavering, even leading Khan to honor him by featuring Shera's security company logo in his film 'Bodyguard'.
title: Know everything about Salman Khan’s bodyguard Shera

description: In his 100th IPL match, Rahul Tripathi's spectacular catch stole the show during the CSK versus LSG game at Ekana Stadium. Tripathi's athletic dive at mid-off dismissed Aiden Markram off Khaleel Ahmed's delivery, giving CSK a brilliant start after they chose to bowl. CSK made two changes, including Shaik Rasheed and Jamie Overton, while LSG brought back Mitchell Marsh.
title: Rahul Tripathi's stunning catch lights up his 100th IPL game - Watch

description: Despite a batting failure in Delhi Capitals' loss to Mumbai Indians, KL Rahul's heartwarming post-match gesture towards fans in wheelchairs went viral. He posed for photos, signed autographs, and interacted with supporters, showcasing his kindness. This act of compassion became the highlight, overshadowing the team's defeat and highlighting the human aspect of sports.
title: Watch: KL Rahul's heartwarming fan moment steals the spotlight

description: Punjab Kings face a setback as Lockie Ferguson is likely out for the remainder of IPL 2025 due to a serious left thigh injury sustained against Sunrisers Hyderabad. Fast bowling coach James Hopes confirmed Ferguson's indefinite absence, creating a void in Punjab's pace attack. The team will now consider replacements like Xavier Bartlett, Azmatullah Omarzai, Vijaykumar Vyshak, and Yash Thakur.
title: Big blow for Punjab Kings! Hopes gives update on Ferguson’s injury

description: Clashes broke out in West Bengal's South 24 Parganas between ISF supporters and police during protests against the Waqf (Amendment) Act. The violence escalated when police prevented protestors from marching to a rally, resulting in torched vehicles, injuries, and arrests. This follows similar unrest in Murshidabad, prompting calls for central intervention and deployment of central forces.
title: Fresh violence hits Bengal: Vehicles torched, many hurt in anti-Waqf stir

description: Chennai Super Kings made changes for their match against Lucknow Super Giants. Ravichandran Ashwin was dropped from the team. Jamie Overton and Shaik Rasheed replaced Ashwin and Devon Conway. MS Dhoni wanted to bowl first due to dew. Lucknow Super Giants included Mitchell Marsh. Rishabh Pant also wanted to bowl first. CSK aimed to improve their performance after recent losses.
title: IPL: Why R Ashwin was dropped against Lucknow Super Giants

description: Katy Perry, Gayle King, and Lauren Sánchez soared into space aboard a Blue Origin rocket from West Texas, marking the company's 11th human flight. The all-female crew, including Aisha Bowe, Amanda Nguyn, and Kerianne Flynn, saw Perry express her mission as boundary-breaking, inspiring young girls to dream big.
title: Katy Perry, Bezos' fiancé and all-female crew back on Earth after reaching space

description: An all-female crew, including notable figures like Aisha Bowe and Katy Perry, is set to launch on Blue Origin's historic space mission on April 14. The crew will wear custom-designed astronaut suits by Monse, tailored for both function and style.
title: Lauren Sanchez, Katy Perry in 'Sexy' Astronaut Suits for Blue Origin's flight
Waqf violent protest: On a tough legal wicket, TMC faces a delicate balancing act

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi met Rampal Kashyap, an admirer who vowed to remain barefoot until Modi became Prime Minister and they met. At a Haryana rally, Modi fulfilled Kashyap's 14-year vow by personally putting shoes on him. While acknowledging the affection, Modi urged supporters to channel their devotion into social work and nation-building projects during his visit to Haryana.
title: Watch: PM Modi helps barefoot admirer fulfil 14-year vow

description: Mehul Choksi, a key figure in the Rs 13,000 crore PNB fraud, has been arrested in Belgium following an extradition request by Indian probe agencies. This action against Choksi, follows the arrest of his nephew Nirav Modi. The PNB scam, involving fraudulent Letters of Undertaking, was exposed in 2018, revealing systemic loopholes.
title: How Mehul Choksi and Nirav Modi pulled off multi-billion-dollar PNB scam

description: Fugitive diamond merchant Mehul Choksi, wanted in India for allegedly defrauding Punjab National Bank (PNB) of nearly Rs 14,000 crore, has been arrested in Belgium. His legal team is contesting extradition, citing the case's political nature and Choksi's poor health, including cancer treatment and PTSD from a prior alleged kidnapping.
title: How Mehul Choksi plans to resist extradition to India from Belgium

description: A plea has been filed in the Supreme Court seeking a court-monitored SIT investigation into the Murshidabad violence during anti-Waqf law protests. The petition also seeks protection for vulnerable lives and properties. Following the violence, the Calcutta High Court ordered CAPF deployment. Authorities are working to restore peace, with some families returning home.
title: Anti-Waqf protests: Plea in SC seeks SIT probe into Murshidabad violence

description: Australia’s sweeping student visa reforms, aimed at reducing net migration, have sparked concern among Indian students and education stakeholders. Stricter rules and a sharp drop in approvals — with Indian visas falling by 48% — have raised fears of discrimination and policy opacity. The move also risks straining Indo-Australian ties and weakening Australia’s global education appeal.
title: Dreams on hold: Indian students face the heat of Australia’s visa overhaul

description: In the last week, on-field umpires have checked bats of multiple players during the Indian Premier League (IPL). Shimron Hetmyer, Hardik Pandya and Phil Salt have all had their bats checked at different times in IPL matches. What is the reason behind the interruptions in play?
title: Explained: Why are umpires randomly checking bats in the IPL?

description: Amidst protests against new Waqf laws and claims of communal violence in Murshidabad, West Bengal minister Firhad Hakim downplayed the situation, stating that people are relocating within the state, not fleeing. BJP leader Suvendu Adhikari alleges that over 400 Hindus were forced to leave their homes due to the violence, blaming Trinamool Congress' appeasement policies.
title: 'Migrating within Bengal': TMC minister's odd claim amid anti-Waqf riots

description: The football world mourns the sudden passing of LSU's Kyren Lacy, prompting heartfelt tributes from NFL stars like Russell Wilson and Ja'Marr Chase. Teammates, including Jayden Daniels and Amik Robertson, shared personal memories and touching final messages, highlighting Lacy's profound impact on and off the field. The LSU community rallies to honor his legacy, remembering his spirit and work ethic.
title: NFL world mourns Kyren Lacy as players like Wilson lead emotional tributes

description: Tahawwur Rana, the alleged mastermind of the 26/11 Mumbai attacks, is currently being interrogated by the NIA for up to ten hours daily. Extradited from the US, Rana is held in a high-security cell in Delhi. The NIA aims to uncover the broader conspiracy behind the attacks that killed 166. Rana is cooperating, and has requested a pen, some paper or a notepad, and a copy of the Quran.
title: NIA grilling Rana for 8-10 hours daily to uncover 'larger conspiracy' behind 26/11 attacks

description: Prime Minister Modi laid the foundation for a Rs 410-crore terminal at Hisar Airport, enhancing Haryana's connectivity. New flights will connect Hisar to Ayodhya, Jammu, Ahmedabad, Jaipur, and Chandigarh. Since 2014, the number of airports has doubled to 150, with the UDAN scheme connecting 90 airports and making air travel more accessible.
title: PM lays foundation stone for new terminal at Hisar airport

description: Pashupati Kumar Paras, chief of the RLJP, declared his party's departure from the NDA, citing perceived injustice and neglect. Paras highlighted the party's loyalty since 2014 but expressed disappointment over being ignored in recent NDA meetings in Bihar. The RLJP is now preparing for the 2025 state assembly elections and open to considering alliances with the INDIA bloc if given due respect.
title: 'They did injustice': Pashupati Kumar Paras announces RLJP's exit from NDA

description: Delhi Capitals faced a defeat against Mumbai Indians, ending their winning streak. Despite the loss, the team's spirit remained high. Skipper Axar Patel encouraged the team to stay positive. Coach Hemang Badani praised individual performances, especially Karun Nair's impressive return. The team is focused on maintaining momentum and looking ahead to future games.
title: 'We are allowed to lose, smile': DC captain's dressing room message

description: Mumbai Indians secured a crucial win against Delhi Capitals in IPL 2025. Post-match discussions focused on Rohit Sharma's possible tactical role. Sanjay Bangar credited Sharma for a key decision. Sanjay Manjrekar argued that Hardik Pandya, as captain, deserved the credit. The debate sparked discussions among fans regarding team leadership. The incident highlights the dynamics within the Mumbai Indians camp.
title: 'Credit should go to Hardik, not Rohit': Commentators spark debate

description: Rajat Patidar silenced critics after being appointed RCB captain, transforming the team into a dominant force with four wins in six matches. Despite initial doubts and comparisons to Virat Kohli, Patidar's calm yet aggressive leadership, blending Dhoni-esque composure with Kohli's intent, has revitalized RCB.
title: 'Rajat Patidar's captaincy a mix of Virat Kohli & MS Dhoni'

description: The BJP strongly criticized Jharkhand minister Hafizul Hassan for his "a Muslim keeps the Quran in his heart and the Constitution in his hand" remarks, deeming them an insult to Indian democracy. Speaking on the ongoing Waqf protests Hassan had said that Muslims hold the Quran in their hearts and the Constitution in their hands. The BJP accused the INDIA bloc of harboring individuals who prioritize religious law. Hassan had alleged the Centre is targeting Muslims and warns of potential unrest.
title: 'Shariat first, then Constitution': JMM minister sparks row, BJP hits back
When Choksi was honeytrapped & kidnapped from Caribbean island

description: President Trump is set to introduce tariffs on imported semiconductors, potentially reshaping the electronics trade. This follows a temporary reprieve for smartphones and computers from reciprocal tariffs on China. Trump emphasized the need to bolster domestic chip production and hinted at possible exemptions, while a national security investigation into the semiconductor sector is underway.
title: How Apple and other tech companies’ ‘problems’ may not be over yet
India has requested fugitive Mehul Choksi's extradition, confirms Belgium

description: Abhishek and Abhinandan Lodha have settled their dispute. The dispute was regarding the use of 'Lodha' and 'Lodha Group' brand names. Macrotech Developers will own the 'Lodha' brand. Abhinandan will retain the 'House of Abhinandan Lodha' brand. Both groups will operate independently. The Bombay High Court had appointed a mediator. The mediator helped in resolving the matter.
title: Lodha brothers resolve disputes over brand names

description: Narendra Modi praised Kerala's Sankaran Nair for his fight against British rule. This was after the 1919 Jallianwala Bagh tragedy. Modi wants people in Punjab, Haryana, and Himachal to know Nair's story. A film on Nair's legal battle, "Keasari 2", is releasing soon. Nair resigned from the Viceroy's Executive Council in protest.
title: PM Modi hails Sankaran Nair ahead of 'Kesari 2' release

description: Fugitive diamond merchant Mehul Choksi, wanted in connection with the Rs 14,000 crore PNB scam, has been arrested in Belgium following renewed extradition efforts by Indian probe agencies. After evading authorities since 2018, Choksi was detained from a hospital where he was receiving medical treatment. Indian agencies are completing extradition procedures, while Choksi may seek relief on medical grounds.
title: PNB scam: How Mehul Choksi was tracked down and arrested in Belgium

description: A leaked Karnataka caste census report proposing increased OBC and Muslim reservations has ignited controversy within the Congress government. The report suggests raising OBC reservation to 51% and Muslims to 8%, sparking accusations of being "unscientific." Vokkaligas and Lingayats are recommended 7% and 8% quotas, respectively. With total reservations potentially reaching 73.
title: 'Unscientific, junk it': Karnataka caste census report divides Congress

description: In Muzaffarnagar, Uttar Pradesh, a shocking incident occurred where a 20-year-old woman was allegedly assaulted and stripped of her hijab, while her male companion was beaten. The attack, captured in a viral video, took place in Khalapar as they returned from collecting a loan EMI.
title: UP woman stripped off hijab, Hindu man beaten in Muzaffarnagar; 6 held

description: Delhi Capitals' winning streak ended abruptly against Mumbai Indians amidst on-field tension and off-field violence. A fan brawl marred the match, raising concerns about stadium security, while a collision between Karun Nair and Jasprit Bumrah ignited a heated exchange. Adding to Delhi's woes, captain Axar Patel was fined for a slow over-rate, impacting their standing in the league.
title: Watch: Fists fly in the stands as fight erupts at Arun Jaitley Stadium

description: Apple's iPhone production in India has surged by 60% to $22 billion, now accounting for one in five iPhones globally. This shift, driven by geopolitical tensions and supply chain vulnerabilities, positions India as a key export hub. Foxconn is expanding its manufacturing footprint in Uttar Pradesh, signaling a long-term commitment to India's growing industrial ecosystem.
title: $22bn pivot: How Apple's India bet is paying off amid US-China trade war

description: Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge has strongly criticized the BJP, labeling them as historical and current adversaries of B.R. Ambedkar. This retort followed PM Modi's accusation that Congress spreads "votebank ka virus" by opposing the Waqf Amendment Act.
title: 'Enemies of Babasaheb': Kharge counters PM Modi's 'votebank ka virus' charge

description: Sunny Deol's 'Jaat' is performing strongly at the box office, showing significant growth over its opening weekend, particularly on Sunday. The film has earned Rs 41.47 crore in India and is approaching the Rs 50 crore mark, potentially boosted by the Ambedkar Jayanti holiday. In the south centres, 'Jaat' is facing competition from Ajith Kumar's 'Good Bad Ugly'.
title: 'Jaat' box office collection: Sunny Deol starrer to 'hold steady', cross Rs 50cr

description: JP Morgan Chase CEO Jamie Dimon advised young investors to focus on America's promising future, citing its vast wealth and potential advancements in health and technology. He stressed prioritizing mental and physical well-being, alongside treating others with respect.
title: JPMorgan Chase CEO disagrees that America's next gen is in bad shape

description: Bengaluru is witnessing a surge in incidents involving youths brandishing machetes and performing dangerous stunts, prompting concern from law enforcement and mental health experts. Recent arrests highlight a troubling trend of aggression and weapon possession among adolescents. Psychiatrists attribute this behavior to unresolved emotional issues and urge parents to be vigilant and seek professional help when needed.
title: Machete-wielding teens on bikes: Rising trend in Bengaluru alarms cops

description: Mehul Choksi, wanted in connection with the Rs 13,000 crore PNB loan fraud, has been arrested in Belgium following a request from India for his extradition. This development follows the removal of an Interpol Red Notice and renewed efforts by Indian authorities to bring him back. Choksi had previously fled to Antigua and Dominica after the scam's exposure.
title: From Antigua to Belgium: Will fugitive Mehul Choksi finally be extradited to India?

description: Fugitive diamond merchant Mehul Choksi, wanted in the PNB scam, has been apprehended in Belgium. India faces an uphill battle for his extradition, as Choksi is likely to cite health issues to resist returning. Whistleblower Hariprasad SV doubts Choksi's return, given his resources and legal support. Nirav Modi, also implicated, remains jailed in London, fighting extradition.
title: Mehul Choksi undergoing cancer treatment, to seek bail - Top developments

description: OpenAI CEO Sam Altman is actively recruiting individuals with expertise in infrastructure, large-scale computing systems, compiler design, and programming language design to join his team. Altman emphasizes the importance of adaptability and continuous learning in the age of AI, suggesting students focus on these skills rather than specific technical knowledge.
title: ChatGPT maker OpenAI CEO Sam Altman makes 'desperate' job offer

description: Delhi Airport's Terminal 2 will close for repairs on April 15, 2025, prompting airlines like IndiGo and Akasa to shift operations to Terminal 1, which will then operate at full capacity. DIAL is trialing baggage transfers between T3 and T1 to ease connections, aiming for a 120-minute transfer time from T1 to T3, despite the lack of an air train.
title: IGI Airport T2 to shut for repairs from tomorrow; flights to shift to T1

description: Four U.S. individuals, known as the "Cutthroat Cowboys," face charges after riding horses through a Walmart in Baker, Louisiana. A viral video captured the group startling customers and staff, leading to public outcry and a police investigation. Mason Webb stated their actions were for amusement and social media attention, claiming the horse as an emotional support animal.
title: 'My emotional support animal': Four charged after riding horses through Walmart

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi launched a strong critique of the Congress party on Monday, accusing them of exploiting the Constitution for political gain and neglecting Dr. BR Ambedkar's vision. He highlighted the Emergency and alleged politicization of reservations. Modi contrasted this with the BJP's development-focused approach.
title: 'Votebank ka virus': PM Modi attacks Congress for opposing Waqf Act

description: Despite stricter US immigration policies, Indian students' interest in US higher education, especially STEM and AI programs, remains strong. A surge in applications to top universities indicates enduring appeal, driven by research opportunities and post-graduation prospects. Experts advise proactive planning and strategic visa applications amidst uncertainties, emphasizing adaptability and early job market preparation.
title: Indians in US: Students urged caution about social media posts

description: Lauren Sánchez led an all-female crew, including Katy Perry and Gayle King, on Blue Origin's New Shepard rocket on April 14, 2025. The NS-31 mission, part of Blue Origin's initiative to democratize space travel, reached past the Kármán line. This launch precedes Sánchez's summer wedding to Jeff Bezos in Venice, with a star-studded guest list.
title: Jeff Bezos' fiancée Lauren Sánchez and Katy Perry to launch into space

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi inaugurated a commercial flight from Hisar to Ayodhya and laid the foundation for a new terminal at Maharaja Agrasen Airport, costing over ₹410 crore. This initiative aims to enhance air travel accessibility with modern facilities, including a cargo terminal and ATC building, expected to be completed in two years.
title: PM Modi flags off first commercial flight to Ayodhya from Hisar

description: Zuhail Ahmed, a Hebbal resident, attempted suicide outside Raj Bhavan, alleging harassment related to a domestic violence case filed by his wife in Chikkaballapura. He claimed the police weren't listening to his complaints and that there were attempts to harm him.
title: Bengaluru techie tries to set himself on fire outside near governor's house

description: PNB scam whistleblower Hariprasad SV expressed concerns about Mehul Choksi's extradition to India, citing his history of evading legal proceedings and access to top-tier European lawyers. Choksi's recent arrest in Belgium has sparked preparations for extradition, but he is expected to mount a strong legal defense, challenging the process based on health and other factors.
title: 'His wallet is full': PNB scam whistleblower reacts to Mehul Choksi's arrest in Belgium

description: Salman Khan is facing a new death threat, received via a WhatsApp message to Mumbai's Transport Department, warning of an attack on his house and a bomb threat to his car. Following this, a police complaint has been filed, and authorities are investigating the threat's origin. As of now, it's not clear if this threat has come from Lawrence Bishnoi.
title: 'Message warned to blow up vehicle': Salman Khan receives another death threat

description: Donald Trump, following a UFC event in Miami, playfully introduced his granddaughter, Kai Trump to reporters labelling them as "fake news" during a 2 am pressor aboard Air Force One. Kai, a competitive golfer committed to the University of Miami, was accompanied by her brothers. The event drew a crowd of political and tech figures, including Elon Musk and Robert F. Kennedy Jr.
title: 'The fake news': Trump's granddaughter Kai joins him at 2am presser- video

description: Call of Duty: Black Ops II, released in 2012, eerily mirrors current US-China tensions in 2025. The game's plot, featuring economic warfare and cyberattacks, strikingly resembles real-world events, including trade disputes and concerns over rare earth elements. Social media users have noted the game's predicted dates aligning with present-day geopolitical developments.
title: This 2012 video game predicted the 2025 US–China trade war

description: Kannada cinema lost a beloved figure as veteran comedy actor Bank Janardhan passed away at 79 due to prolonged illness and multi-organ complications. Known for his impeccable comic timing and character roles in over 500 films, including Shhh! and Tarle Nan Maga, he also charmed audiences through television serials like Papa Pandu.
title: Veteran Kannada comedy actor Bank Janardhan passes away at 79

description: In a bizarre scheme of things in the Pakistan Super League 2025, James Vince of Karachi Kings received a hair dryer as the 'Reliable Player' award after his match-winning century against Multan Sultans. Vince's explosive 101 off 43 balls, coupled with Khushdil Shah's 60, powered Karachi to a record-breaking chase of 235.
title: Vince gets hair dryer as reward for century; netizens can't stop laughing

description: Ambedkar Jayanti, observed annually on April 14th, commemorates the birth of Dr. B.R. Ambedkar, a pivotal figure in India's social reform and the architect of its Constitution. The day honors his relentless fight against caste discrimination and his advocacy for equality, liberty, and fraternity. Celebrations include tributes, rallies, and discussions, reinforcing his enduring legacy of social justice and empowerment.
title: Ambedkar Jayanti: 50+ wishes, messages, quotes, images to share

description: "At present, China's exports are facing a complex and severe external situation, but 'the sky will not fall'," the spokesperson said, news agency Reuters. He also stated that China is "actively building a diversified market, deepening cooperation with all parties in the supply chain," and added, "Importantly, China's domestic demand market is broad."
title: China says exports facing severe external situation, but 'sky will not fall'

description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy has urged Donald Trump to visit Ukraine before making decisions about the conflict with Russia, emphasizing the need to witness the devastation firsthand. Zelenskyy insists that a visit would help Trump understand Vladimir Putin's intentions and the true nature of the war. This appeal comes amid ongoing efforts to find a resolution, with Trump expressing concern over a recent Russian strike in Sumy.
title: 'Come see kids, hospitals': Zelenskyy urges Trump to visit Ukraine before talks

description: In a joint operation, the Indian Coast Guard and Gujarat ATS seized over 300kg of narcotics worth approximately Rs 1,800 crore. The ICG ship intercepted a transshipment attempt near the International Maritime Boundary Line based on intelligence from Gujarat ATS. While the suspects fled across the IMBL, the ICG recovered the jettisoned narcotics.
title: Indian Coast Guard and Gujarat ATS intercept over 300kg narcotics

description: Indian stock exchanges will be closed on Monday for Dr BR Ambedkar Jayanti. Last week, the markets closed positively, recovering from an initial decline triggered by US-China tariff concerns. Investors are now awaiting corporate earnings reports from major companies like Wipro, Infosys, HDFC Bank, and ICICI Bank in the holiday-shortened week.
title: Stock Markets closed on April 14 for Ambedkar Jayanti

description: During Sunday's IPL 2025 match between Delhi Capitals and Mumbai Indians, Karun Nair's impressive 89 off 40 balls was overshadowed by a heated argument with Jasprit Bumrah following an on-field spat. Despite Nair's efforts, Mumbai Indians secured a 12-run victory, powered by Tilak Varma's 59 and contributions from other batters.
title: WATCH: Bumrah, Karun have heated exchange during DC vs MI

description: Los Angeles Dodgers pitcher Alex Vesia and his wife Kayla joyfully announced they are expecting a baby, sharing the news through an adorable Instagram reel and a beautiful photoshoot. Similarly, New York Mets' Pete Alonso and his wife Haley also revealed their pregnancy, expressing their excitement about becoming parents in 2025.
title: Dodgers’ Alex Vesia pulls out new mom to be Kayla’s ultrasound snaps
PNB bank loan 'fraud' case: Fugitive businessman Mehul Choksi arrested in Belgium

description: Lakshmibai College's principal, Pratyush Vatsala, applied cow dung to classroom walls in Block C to combat the heat, aiming for an eco-friendly solution amidst infrastructure issues. This unconventional method, intended as an internal update, sparked debate on social media, highlighting the need for better facilities like fans and coolers in older buildings.
title: To combat heat, DU principal applies cow dung on classroom walls, sparks row
India tests laser system to destroy aerial targets

description: Sunny Deol's latest film, 'Jaat,' is performing well at the box office, particularly after a significant surge in numbers on Sunday. 'Jaat' has collected ₹40.25 crore in total. While it cannot be compared to 'Gadar 2,' it is giving tough competition to Salman Khan's 'Sikandar,' which has seen a drop in business.
title: 'Jaat' box office collection day 4: Sunny Deol starrer sees a huge growth
Kernel of calm for Goa's cashew business as Trump hits 90-day pause on higher tariffs

description: Anna Lezhneva, wife of Pawan Kalyan, demonstrated her devotion by donating her hair at the Sri Venkateswara Swamy temple in Tirumala. This act of faith follows a challenging period for the family, as their son, Mark Shankar, recovers from burn injuries sustained in a recent school fire in Singapore. Her gesture has garnered widespread admiration and support on social media.
title: Pawan Kalyan’s wife donates hair at Tirumala amid son’s recovery

description: Top Trump trade advisor Peter Navarro downplayed his public feud with Tesla CEO Elon Musk, dismissing Musk's 'moron' jab. Despite Musk's criticism of Navarro's trade policies and questioning his credentials, Navarro claimed there's no issue between them. The White House has acknowledged the differing views on trade, seemingly unconcerned by the public spat between the two high-profile figures.
title: Trump's key trade adviser responds to Musk calling him 'moron' and 'dumber' …
Furore over Karnataka caste survey data, many ministers call it ‘unscientific’
Mother kills girl over relation with man from different caste

description: President Trump reaffirmed his tough stance on trade, asserting that no country, particularly China, would escape tariffs. He dismissed claims of exemptions for tech products, clarifying they were reclassifications subject to existing tariffs. Trump vowed to investigate the electronics supply chain, aiming to end perceived trade abuses and restore America's economic strength through new policies.
title: ‘No one off the hook’: Trump denies tariff rollback, hits China, tech
Silchar protesters hurl stones at cops, get lathi charged
